Wesley Ryan parted with his beloved 1993 Ford Mustang to pay for his wife’s medical bills. CAPE TOWN - US siblings reduced their father to tears when they presented him with a car he had sold about 12 years ago when their mother was diagnosed with cancer and needed surgery. Wesley Ryan parted with his beloved 1993 Ford Mustang to pay for his wife’s medical bills. The siblings, who had fond memories of the car, wanted to show their appreciation to their father for his sacrifice. The father was overcome with emotion when he saw the car.  